Development Roadmap — ESI.ts v3.4.0
=====================================

Completed
---------

[x] ESI Spec 1:1 Endpoint Coverage
    170 GET + 35 non-GET endpoints across 32 domain clients.
    Automated validation via `npm run validate:esi` against live ESI swagger spec.

[x] API Verb Handling
    All HTTP verbs explicitly passed; POST/PUT/DELETE bodies JSON-serialized.
    Status-specific handling for 201, 204, 304, 420, 429, 5xx.

[x] Models
    Type-safe request/response models. EsiError class with typed status checks.
    TestDataFactory provides comprehensive mock models for all domains.

[x] Caching
    ETag-based caching with If-None-Match, Cache-Control max-age TTL,
    stale-on-error for 5xx, write invalidation, LRU eviction, auto-cleanup.

[x] Rate Limiting
    Floating-window (X-Ratelimit-*) + legacy error-limit (x-esi-error-limit-*).
    Token costs per spec, proactive deceleration, hard block on 420/429.

[x] Pagination
    Offset-based (page=N) with retry logic and empty-page detection.
    Cursor-based (before/after tokens) for Freelance Jobs with polling support.

[x] Testing
    74 suites, 577+ tests. All verbs covered. BDD scenarios included.
    Coverage thresholds enforced in CI.


Recently Completed
------------------

[x] User-Agent Version Fix
    Centralized in src/core/constants.ts as 'esi.ts/3.4.0'. Updated across
    ApiRequestHandler, PaginationHandler, CursorPaginationHandler, MetaClient.

[x] Datasource Parameter
    EsiClientConfig accepts datasource: 'tranquility' | 'singularity'.
    Also reads from ESI_DATASOURCE env var. Appended to all endpoint URLs.

[x] Cache Hit Rate Tracking
    ETagCacheManager now tracks hits/misses. getStats() returns actual
    hitRate, hits, and misses. Counters reset on clear().

[x] Input Validation
    Path params validated for empty values, unsafe characters (path traversal,
    query injection), and non-finite numbers. Query params validated for
    null/undefined, non-finite numbers, and excessive length.

[x] Deprecation Handling
    EndpointDefinition supports deprecated?: { message, replacedBy, sunsetDate }.
    Logs a warning via logger on each call to a deprecated endpoint.


[x] Token Refresh
    EsiClientConfig accepts onTokenRefresh callback (TokenProvider).
    On 401, the handler automatically refreshes and retries once.
    Concurrent refreshes are coalesced into a single provider call.
    Also available via EsiClient.setTokenProvider() at runtime.

[x] Clean Architecture: HeadersUtil Pure Function
    Replaced static HeadersUtil class (globally mutable state) with
    parseHeaders() pure function returning ParsedHeaders interface.
    Eliminates concurrent-request data corruption risk.

[x] Clean Architecture: Decompose executeRequest
    Broke monolithic executeRequest (216 lines, 9 responsibilities) into
    focused helpers: buildRequestHeaders, handleEarlyStatus,
    tryStaleCacheResponse, cacheResponse, parseJsonBody,
    handleCursorPagination, handleOffsetPagination.

[x] Clean Architecture: Extract Interfaces
    ICache, IRateLimiter, ILogger interfaces extracted from concrete
    implementations. ETagCacheManager implements ICache, RateLimiter
    implements IRateLimiter. Logger supports setLogger() for custom
    ILogger implementations. All interfaces exported from index.ts.


[x] Request Middleware / Interceptors
    RequestInterceptor and ResponseInterceptor types. MiddlewareManager
    handles ordered execution. Configured via EsiClientConfig or at
    runtime via addRequestInterceptor()/addResponseInterceptor().
    Interceptors receive typed context (url, method, headers, body,
    durationMs, fromCache) and return modified context.

[x] Circuit Breaker
    CircuitBreaker with closed→open→half-open state machine. Tracks
    consecutive 5xx failures per endpoint path. Configurable threshold,
    reset timeout, and half-open probe attempts. Enabled via
    enableCircuitBreaker in EsiClientConfig. Stats and reset via
    getCircuitBreakerStats()/resetCircuitBreaker().

[x] Dependency Injection
    ApiClient holds optional ICache, IRateLimiter, CircuitBreaker.
    executeRequest resolves dependencies from client first, falls back
    to global singletons. Each EsiClient instance can have its own
    cache, rate limiter, and circuit breaker. Enables mock injection
    for testing without global state pollution.


Remaining Gaps
--------------

    No remaining architectural gaps identified. All items from the
    original roadmap and clean architecture audit are complete.